## Key Considerations
- "Static" means the transformer weights are frozen/distilled into a simpler architecture
- Much faster than full transformer inference but quality trades off
- MRL support: embeddings can be truncated to lower dims with controlled quality loss
- Re-normalization after truncation is CRITICAL (truncated vectors are not unit length)
- The 397x speed claim needs independent verification in our benchmark

## MRL Dimension Analysis
The benchmark should test at multiple truncation levels:
- 768 dims (full, best quality)
- 512 dims (moderate truncation)
- 256 dims (aggressive, good speed/quality tradeoff)
- 128 dims (very aggressive, significant quality loss expected)
- 64 dims (extreme, mostly for testing graceful degradation)

